{"questionId":"27630","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a circle with a diameter&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>&nbsp;has coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> has&nbsp;coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The circle forms the base of a right cone whose vertex <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>V</mtext></math> has coordinates&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e89450a6f7b680da510617ae3802081d69c70003.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the exact volume of the cone.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find the distance between their centre and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>V</mtext></math>&nbsp;(the perpendicular height of the cone)&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mtext>their&nbsp;slant&nbsp;height</mtext></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mtext>their&nbsp;radius</mtext></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>20</mn></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>Volume&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><msqrt><mn>20</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>20</mn></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27630","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.3b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the exact volume of the cone.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}